 :tx/rationale "FIRST PRINCIPLES ANALYSIS of the 'phantom decision' failure mode. The fundamental problem: DECISIONS and TASKS are different entity types that SHOULD be linked but AREN'T. When I observe 'DESIGN DECISION: implement X with approach Y', that creates an :observation/* entity. When I create a task 'implement X', that creates a :task/* entity. But there is NO automatic link between them. The decision references work that should become a task, but the system doesn't detect this. THREE-LAYER GUARD analysis: (1) PREVENTION (structural): Currently NOTHING prevents decisions from being orphaned — the data model doesn't enforce decision-to-task linkage. (2) DETECTION (observational): Currently NO mechanism detects orphaned decisions at harvest time. The harvest pipeline looks for harvestable knowledge but doesn't check whether decisions have corresponding tasks. (3) CORRECTION (adaptive): Currently NO learning loop — the system doesn't track decision-to-task linkage rate or improve it over time. ALL THREE LAYERS ARE MISSING. This is why the failure mode recurred across TWO sessions."
